page.description: The result is TRUE if the expressions on both sides of the operator are not equal, i.e. if both Operand1 and Operand2 are of different types or have different values.
page.syntax: Result as L = Operand1 as A <> Operand2 as A

argument.name: Operand1
argument.description: A value or expression of any type.

argument.name: Operand2
argument.description: A value or expression of any type.

section.note: The Not Equal To operator is not case-sensitive and removes any trailing blanks before the strings are compared.
